Data Requirements

FluentData LLC has been contracted to compile all data (fill this in)

Data Source

U.S. EPAs Air Quality System website was used to obtain a list of all air quality monitors in the country. This file was obtained from the following location: http://aqsdr1.epa.gov/aqsweb/aqstmp/airdata/aqs_monitors.zip most recently on March 24, 2016. The data was then processed using the R programming language to subset and visualize the parameters of interest for the State of Indiana. The remainder of this document will outline the available data.

Data Cleaning and Filtering

The raw dataset downloaded from U.S. EPA contained 300400 records. Each record represents a monitor with data in AQS. Basic cleanup of this data was done, including ensuring that date columns were formatted as dates and an index column was created by concatenating the State.Code, County.Code, Site.Number, and POC columns.

Next, any rows with missing date ranges were removed, as well as any rows where the Last.Sample.Date was before January 1, 1999. Lastly, the dataset was reduced to only records from Indiana (State.Code == 18). This filtering left 5685 rows of data.

Ozone (44201)

There are 60 ozone monitors in Indiana that have been active at some point between 1999 and 2015. Of these, 46 were active as of the end of 2015 and 22 have been active during the entire period covered by this project (1999-2015).

Below is a plot illustrating ozone data coverage, by monitor, for all monitors that collected ozone data during the period of interest.

Many EPA air pollutant monitors are placed relative to specific sources and so are not representative of general concentrations or population exposures. Below is a table showing the reported purpose of ozone monitors in Indiana.
